HEADWORD: Pumpernickel
<hw>Pump"er*nick`el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.]</ety>
<def>A sort of bread, made of unbolted rye, which forms the chief food
of the Westphalian peasants. It is acid but nourishing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

